# fe4cac67383d464790167f5ebc8ed961
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/getting-started/index.en.rst:68
msgid ""
"You compile your plugin source code to create a shared library that "
"Traffic Server loads when it is started. Your plugin contains callback "
"functions that are registered for specific Traffic Server events. When "
"Traffic Server needs to process an event, it invokes any and all call-"
"back functions you've registered for that event type."
msgstr ""

# a564a9894842484fb472b958b2b7cce9
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/getting-started/index.en.rst:76
msgid ""
"Since plugins add object code to Traffic Server, programming errors in a "
"plugin can have serious implications. Bugs in your plugin, such as an "
"out-of-range pointer, can cause Traffic Server processes to crash and may"
" ultimately result in unpredictable behavior."
msgstr ""

